requests per day and 15 requests per minute. * Special Ability: Massive Context. You can have a Shortcut that
"scrapes" a long article or your entire day’s calendar and sends the whole thing to Gemini for a summary in one
go. * iOS Vibe: Very easy to parse its JSON response in Shortcuts. 2. OpenRouter (Free Tier) OpenRouter is a
"unified" API. You get one API key that lets you access multiple free models (Llama 3.3, Mistral, Gemma 2, etc.). *
The "Lot": They aggregate over 18+ completely free models. If one model hits a limit, you just change the model
ID in your Shortcut and keep going. * Special Ability: Model Diversity. You can use specialized coding models (like
Devstral 2) or reasoning models (like DeepSeek-R1) all via the same URL. * iOS Vibe: Use the model ID suffix :free
to ensure you never get billed. 3. GroqCloud If your Shortcut needs to feel "instant" (e.g., a voice-to-text reply),
Groq is the winner. * The "Lot": High RPM (Requests Per Minute) limits. While they have daily token caps, the
speed is the real draw. * Special Ability: Latency. It generates text at 300+ tokens per second. Your Shortcut will
finish running before you even lock your phone. * iOS Vibe: Best for "Hey Siri" triggers where you don't want to
wait 5 seconds for a response. 4. Cloudflare Workers AI Cloudflare is an infrastructure giant. Their free tier for AI
is designed for high-volume background tasks. * The "Lot": Up to 10,000 free neurons (requests) per day on their
Free plan. * Special Ability: Edge Execution. Since it runs on Cloudflare's global network, the "path" from your
iPhone to the AI is extremely short, making it highly reliable on cellular data. * iOS Vibe: Incredible for small,
repetitive tasks like "Categorize this receipt" or "Translate this clipboard text." 5. Mistral AI (La Plateforme) Mistral
is the pride of European AI and offers a very stable "Experiment" tier. * The "Lot": 1 request per second. That’s
3,600 chats per hour. It’s nearly impossible to hit this limit as a single user. * Special Ability: Efficiency. Their
"Mistral Small" and "Codestral" models are incredibly dense and follow complex instructions better than most
large models. * iOS Vibe: Very clean API documentation makes it easy to set up the Dictionary headers in
Shortcuts. 6. DeepSeek (Official API) The "Logic King" of 2026. DeepSeek-R1 is the model everyone uses for
hard reasoning. * The "Lot": They frequently give out millions of free tokens to new users. For automation, a
million tokens can last for thousands of Shortcut runs. * Special Ability: Chain-of-Thought. You can tell the
Shortcut to "Think deeply before answering," and it will perform complex logic (math/coding) in the background.
7. Sambanova Cloud * The "Lot": Generous free access to Meta’s massive Llama 405B model. * Special Ability:
Full Precision. While other free APIs use "compressed" models, Sambanova runs them at full strength. It is the
"smartest" free Llama access you can get. 8. Together AI * The "Lot": $25 in free credits upon sign-up. In the
